      passage: `<p>By analyzing the level of radioactive decay within a fossil specimen, scientists can establish the age of that fossil with a high degree of precision. When radioactive elements aren&rsquo;t present, scientists turn to _____ analysis of Earth&rsquo;s sediment layers (strata)&mdash;to estimate how old a fossil is based on the age of the strata in which the fossil is found.</p>`,
